article.headline: Buffalo 70, Kent St. 55
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. -- John Boyer scored 18 points, grabbed eight rebounds and dished out six assists as Buffalo snapped Kent State?s eight-game winning streak with a 70-55 win on Saturday. Calvin Betts finished with 15 points and eight rebounds and Rodney Pierce had 14 points and eight boards for the Bulls (14-9, 7-5 Mid-American Conference). Betts had 13 points in the first half, shooting 5-for-6 from the floor and made three 3-pointers before halftime. He led Buffalo's early 14-3 run, helping the Bulls claim a 33-19 lead at halftime. The Bulls, who have won three straight, shot 46.9 percent for the game and converted on 23 of 49 shots from the field. They also shot 6-for-18 from beyond the 3-point arc and 18-for-20 from the foul line. Chris Singletary led Kent State (18-8, 9-3) with 18 points and eight rebounds. The Golden Flashes shot just 34.5 percent from the floor.
